cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.NT, cs.MM, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a network code for the wireless two-way relay channel and derives theoretical error rates, which are typical topics in information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless communication and network coding, which are relevant to networking and internet architecture.
3. cs.NT (Networking and Telecommunications) - The paper focuses on wireless communication and spectral efficiency, which are related to networking and telecommunications.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper uses binary phase shift keying modulation, which is a common technique in multimedia communication.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a practical system model for full duplex physical layer network coding, which can be considered as a system and control problem.
